  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWe had lots of eth nodes and use them to generate address/account.\r\nAnd these addresses would be also used in other private network/chain.\r\n\r\nWhen we want to sign tx for other private chain, we need move the keystore-file from the corresponding eth node to private chain node. this operation is very unsafe. And some potential exception (such as   new-feature-module-logic or network/IO issue) may cause the move error, then tx sign error, .\r\n\r\nSo for now, we want to call eth node _sign api to sign tx, and broadcast the returned rawTx by corresponding private chain.\r\nAll our eth nodes are in our own network env, so no safe issue for us. \r\n\r\nAnd I found the code is deadly written \"fmt.Sprintf(\"\\x19Ethereum Signed Message:\\n%d%s\", len(data), string(data))\" before sign. \r\n\r\nShall I request to add some geth --option to make this prefix dropped ? \r\n\r\n(Also checked the code of eth_signTransaction, would only be able to sign tx for self-chain, since reply protection).\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?",
